# Orchestration Hooks

## When to consult subagents
The main agent invokes subagents at specific workflow steps. Each subagent produces a structured report; the main agent integrates all reports into a single ticket comment.

| Step | Hook | Subagent | What it returns |
|------|------|----------|-----------------|
| 2 | validation | validator-agent | Checklist results: fields present/missing, completeness score |
| 3 | triage | triage-agent | Classification, client, access type, routing, assignment |
| 4 | solution | solution-agent | Related ticket links, solution steps with sources |
| 5 | judge | judge-agent | Quality scorecard, pass/fail, improvement suggestions |

## How to consult
1. Build the consultation prompt using `.cursor/skills/consultation-prompts/SKILL.md`.
2. Pass the prompt to the subagent.
3. Receive the subagent's structured report.
4. If judge returns FAIL (score < 6.0) → re-run solution step with judge feedback (max 2 retries).
5. Integrate all reports into the final comment format defined in agent.md.

## Subagent isolation
- Subagents do NOT see each other's output unless explicitly passed by the main agent.
- Subagents are read-only (see `000-subagent-read-only.mdc`).
